  * update submodule vyatta-op-quagga

  [ Marat Nepomnyashy ]
  * submodule vyatta-cfg-dhcp-server: Properly scan through vif
    addresses to check if any of them fall inside DHCP lease subnets.
    Bug 2447 fix.
  * submodule vyatta-cfg-vpn: Treat ipsec return code 26624 as normal
    when bringing up a connection, but treat all other error codes as
    errors.  Bug 2671 fix.  Also added settings 'nhelpers=5' to mitigate
    Openswan Bug 412 and 'plutowait=yes' to mitigate Openswan Bug 198.
  * submodule vyatta-cfg:  Removed stale init entries for dhcpd,
    dhcrelay, and lighttpd daemons.  Bug 2692 fix.
  * submodule vyatta-cfg-dhcp-relay:  Added checks to determine if the
    DHCP relay interface specified is a vif, and if so, check that the
    vif has been configured.  Part of Bug 2473 fix.
  * submodule vyatta-op-dhcp-server:  Added Perl script 'vyatta-clear-
    dhcp-lease.pl' whose purpose is to clear out a DHCP lease from
    dhcpd.leases file and restart the DHCP server.  Part of Bug 2703
    fix.
  * submodule vyatta-op-dhcp-server: Added appropriate templates and
    modifications for op command 'clear dhcp lease ip <ip>.  Bug 2703
    fix.
  * submodule vyatta-cfg-dhcp-relay: Do not require that at least one
    interface be specified.  Bug 2404 fix.
  * submodule vyatta-cfg-dhcp-relay:  Added checks for interfaces of
    type 'multilink', 'serial', and 'tunnel'.  Bug 2473 fix.
  * submodule vyatta-dhcp3-client:  Do not install default
    'dhclient.conf' as this is generated by the Vyatta config system
  * Properly screen-scrape the 'client-hostname' textual value from
    between the first and last quotation marks.  Bug 2861 fix.
  * Check for the case when authentication mode is not specified to
    prevent Perl uninitialized value error.  Bug 2772 fix.
  * Moved execution of 'show dhcp' commands to '/opt/vyatta/bin/sudo-
    users' so that operator users can execute them.  Bug 2864 fix.
  * Moved execution of 'show vpn' commands to '/opt/vyatta/bin/sudo-
    users' so that operator users can execute them.  Bug 2865 fix.
  * Properly handle the situation when DHCP server does not start when
    its config file is missing.  Part of Bug 2873 fix.
  * Properly restart the DHCP server after clearing out a lease from the
    'dhcpd.leases' file only if the DHCP server has been enabled in the
    configuration.  Bug 2873 fix.
  * Added a setting to disable DHCP server even when config is entered.
    Bug 2599 fix.
  * Fixed up 'clear dhcp leases'.
  * Fixed-up operator commands 'clear vpn ipsec-process' and 'show vpn
    debug detail' so that they no longer require sudo password.
  * Initialize variable and check for invalid args.
  * submodule vyatta-op-vpn:  Call 'gen_local_rsa_key.pl' from
    '/opt/vyatta/bin/sudo-users/' rather than '/opt/vyatta/sbin/'.  Bug
    2883 fix.

